article.headline: Norfolk St. 74, N. Carolina A&amp,T 61
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Michael Deloach scored 23 points and Corey Lyons added 20 to lead Norfolk State to a 74-71 win over North Carolina A&T on Thursday night. With the game tied at 32, Norfolk State (11-17, 9-7 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) scored 8 unanswered points to take a 40-32 lead on a layup by Aleek Pauline with 17:09 to play. The Spartans didn't relinquish the lead the rest of the game. With the win and a 68-62 Coppin State loss to Morgan State, Norfolk State clinched the third seed in the conference tournament, beginning on Tuesday. Kevin Worsley added 11 points and 10 rebounds, Brandon Monroe tallied 13 rebounds and Pauline grabbed 11 for the Spartans, who outrebounded the Aggies (16-15, 9-7) 48-31. Nicholas Wilson and Marc Hill scored 11 points each for North Carolina A&T, which shot 33.3 percent from the field (22-for-66).
